1.when to using final keyword
	 ● if it has an implementation that should not be changed and it is critical to the consistent state of the object.
	 	such us Methods called from constructors should generally be declared final. If a constructor calls a non-final method, 
 		a subclass may redefine that method with surprising or undesirable results.
	 
	 ●you can also declare an entire class final. A class that is declared final cannot be subclassed. 
	 	This is particularly useful, for example, when creating an immutable class like the String class.